          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced through the 2H(d,n)3He",
                "reaction by using a deuterium gas target. The",
                "monoenergetic neutron energy was changed by adjusting",
                "the deuteron beam energy. The deuteron beam current",
                "was about 3.0 mu-A during measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A BF3 long counter as a neutron flux monitor."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Using a double-section gridded ionization",
                "chamber (GIC) as the alpha-particle detector, with a",
                "common cathode. The distance from the cathode to the",
                "grid was 61 mm, and that from the grid to the anode",
                "was 15 mm. The working gas of the GIC was a mixture",
                "gas of krypton with about 3% carbon dioxide."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Alpha particles"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FLUX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron flux was monitored by a BF3 long",
                "counter. The absolute neutron flux at the sample",
                "position was determined by the fission counts from",
                "the 238U(n,f) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
